Generate square waveform on the specified analog output pin. The block input controls the duty cycle of the square waveform. An input value of 0 produces a 0 percent duty cycle, and an input value of 1.0 produces a 100 percent duty cycle.

Captures video from a USB camera using V4L2 driver framework. During simulation, the model outputs a moving colorbar image. While running on hardware, the block outputs video from a USB camera. 

Set Image size parameter to the desired output size. Use Pixel format parameter to specify the format of the output video stream. 

Use parameters in the Advanced tab to adjust the image and device properties.
